<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99893365173944></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99893365173944><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99893365173944>Jewelry and Twisting</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99893365173944#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 27th 1:34 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hiya all, two things to ask about.  First of all, I am a 12th lvl Bard on the Povar server, and I have about 50 plat on me.  What sort of jewelry should I buy?  I have a necklace that ups my charisma to a 115, and a ring that ups my stamina 2 points.  I also have a bracelet that helped to increase my charisma to 115, what else should I get?  Second, as a 12th lvl Bard, what songs should I twist?  I have heard so many different opinions that I dont know what to believe!  :)  However, before you respond to this, please bare in mind that I am currently able to only twist 2 songs at a time.  Thank you very much.  Any help is appreciated.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99901410693345></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99901410693345><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99901410693345>RE: Jewelry and Twisting</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99901410693345#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=15234><span id=Scholar>Mahatma</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>41 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 28th 11:55 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, it depends on how you like to play, if you like to group and use weapons, go with AC and strength gear.  If you like to group and use instruments, go with AC and Dex gear.  Solo, probably just AC and str for now.  In groups, you are going to be getting hit quite a bit while you are learning what songs aggro you the most, so it's a good idea to get your AC as high as you can reasonably afford (bronze or banded at L. 12) before worrying about your other stats.  Strength helps you to hit harder, Dexterity helps you to miss fewer notes, and Charisma helps to mez and charm mobs.  For L. 12, you don't really need to worry about charisma, but it's a good idea to store that cha gear you already got in the bank.  Once you hit level 27, things really start to pick up with the charisma.<br><br>As far as twisting songs goes, I've found it to be easiest to make a hotkey pad of the 3 songs I want to twist (you can do this the same way as you would for Sneak, Hide, etc, except left-click and hold over a song to make the hotkey), make a hotkey of a Gen inventory slot (with a backpack in it) and my 2 melee slots.  The reason why is that later on, you may be twisting different instruments as well as songs.  Start a song, wait for the message that your song has taken effect to pop up, then stop it and as soon as you are able to, start up the next one.  There may be other factors which could cause you to not be able to do this, such as lag.  Normally, I can twist 3, sometimes 4 songs, but on occasion, it has been difficult to keep up just 1 song due to insane lag issues.  For the bard class, having a good connection is more important than having good gear.  Bards can be amazingly effective naked with only their instruments and weapons, in a group.  However, for charming and mezzing purposes, it's best to go ahead and have the gear =)<br><br>Thunderous Silenc<br>40th Bard of the Innoruuk Server<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
