<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99812062229343></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99812062229343><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99812062229343>RE: Newbie questions</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99812062229343#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 18th 3:43 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Go to your inventory slot and right click on a melee item slot (where you see your weapon or shield).  You will see that a copy of that square is now "attatched" to your mouse pointer.  Now press F10 once.  This screen doesn't have the solid grey borders-they're a kinda translucent black.  Put the equipment square on the first hotkey square.  Do this again for the second melee slot and for the first two or three equipment slots.  Don't put backpacks in the first two or three slots, instead, put your instruments.  When you want to change weapons to instruments or vice versa..just pick the items up from your hotkeys :)  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
